<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8' ?><page><modules><textModule left='5' top='5' width='78.6858316221766' height='75.66347469220239' style=''><text><b><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMS_Lion_%281910%29" title="HMS Lion (1910)">HMS <i>Lion</i></a></b> was a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battlecruiser" title="Battlecruiser">battlecruiser</a> of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_Navy" title="Royal Navy">Royal Navy</a>, the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lead_ship" title="Lead ship">lead ship</a> of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lion_class_battlecruiser" title="Lion class battlecruiser">her class</a>. <i>Lion</i> served as the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flagship" title="Flagship">flagship</a> of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grand_Fleet" title="Grand Fleet">Grand Fleet</a>'s battlecruisers throughout World War&nbsp;I, except when she was being refitted or under repair. She sank the German <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Light_cruiser" title="Light cruiser">light cruiser</a> <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SMS_K%C3%B6ln_%281909%29" title="SMS Kln (1909)" class="mw-redirect"><i>Kln</i></a> during the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Heligoland_Bight_%281914%29" title="Battle of Heligoland Bight (1914)">Battle of Heligoland Bight</a> and served as <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vice_Admiral" title="Vice Admiral">Vice Admiral</a> <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Beatty,_1st_Earl_Beatty" title="David Beatty, 1st Earl Beatty">Beatty</a>'s <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flagship" title="Flagship">flagship</a> at the battles of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Dogger_Bank_%281915%29" title="Battle of Dogger Bank (1915)">Dogger Bank</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Jutland" title="Battle of Jutland">Jutland</a>. She was so badly damaged at the first of these battles that she had to be towed back to port by the battlecruiser <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMS_Indomitable_%281907%29" title="HMS Indomitable (1907)"><i>Indomitable</i></a>
